Definition: strike with disgust or revulsion
Example: The scandalous behavior of this married woman shocked her friends
Synonyms: noun, feeling, person, shocker, offend, adj, all, unwholesome, offensive, scandalize, act, scandalization, event, scandal, communication, scandalise, scandalisation, appal, appall, outrage, disgust, strike, with, or, revulsion, The, scandalous, behavior, of, this, married, woman, shocked, her, friends
